  "What is a 'constraint' in an optimization problem?": "",
  "The derivative of the objective function": "",
  "The domain of the function": "",
  "A condition or equation that limits the possible values of the variables": "",
  "The function to be maximized": "",
  "A constraint is an equation or inequality that restricts the variables, such as a fixed perimeter or volume, used to reduce the problem to one variable.": "",
  "What is the 'objective function' in optimization?": "",
  "The second derivative test result": "",
  "The function whose maximum or minimum value is being sought": "",
  "The constraint equation": "",
  "The derivative set to zero": "",
