  "A cable company runs a cable from a power station on shore to an island 6 miles offshore. The island is 9 miles down the coast. Underwater cable costs $400/mile, land cable costs $200/mile. Where should the cable go underwater to minimize cost?": "",
  "9 miles by land then straight across": "",
  "4.5 miles down the coast": "",
  "3*sqrt(3) ≈ 5.2 miles down the coast, then underwater": "",
  "Directly to the island (all underwater)": "",
  "Let x = land distance. Cost = 200x + 400*sqrt((9-x)^2+36). C' = 200 - 400(9-x)/sqrt((9-x)^2+36) = 0. (9-x)/sqrt((9-x)^2+36) = 1/2. 4(9-x)^2 = (9-x)^2+36. 3(9-x)^2 = 36. (9-x)^2 = 12. 9-x = 2sqrt(3). x = 9-2sqrt(3) ≈ 5.54. Actually going underwater from 9-x = 2sqrt(3) ≈ 3.46 miles from shore entry. Land distance x ≈ 5.54 mi.": ""
